{{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = {{PAGENAME}} | synonyms = | image = File:Blausen 0290 DeepVeinThrombosis.png | thumb | | alt = | caption = Deep vein thrombosis is one of the characteristics of this syndrome | pronounce = | field = | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }} '''Hughes–Stovin syndrome''' is a rare [[autoimmune disorder]] of unknown cause that is characterized by the combination of multiple [[lung|pulmonary]] [[artery]] [[aneurysm]]s and [[deep vein thrombosis]]. It is named after the two British [[physician]]s, [[John Patterson Hughes]] and [[Peter George Ingle Stovin]], who first described it in 1959.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Hughes |first1=JP |last2=Stovin |first2=PG |title=Segmental pulmonary artery aneurysms with peripheral venous thrombosis. |journal=British Journal of Diseases of the Chest |date=January 1959 |volume=53 |issue=1 |pages=19-27 |doi=10.1016/S0007-0971(59)80106-6 |pmid=13618502}}</ref> It is a rare variant of [[Behçet's disease]], which entails more general problems with the circulatory system. Most patients are young adult males between the age of 20–40. Common clinical presentations include [[fever]], cough, [[dyspnea]] and [[hemoptysis]]. [[radiology|Radiological]] features are similar to those of Behçet's disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medcyclopaedia.com/library/topics/volume_v_1/h/hughes_stovin_syndrome.aspx|title=Hughes stovin syndrome|publisher=[[General Electric|GE]]|work=Medcyclopaedia}}</ref> There is no satisfactory treatment for this disease.
==Symptoms== * Multiple pulmonary aneurysms<ref name="NCBI">{{cite journal |title=Hughes-Stovin Syndrome: a case report and review of the literature |author=Chalazonitis |date=January 29, 2009 |display-authors=etal |pmc=2649053 |pmid=19178695 |doi=10.1186/1757-1626-2-98 |volume=2 |journal=Cases J |pages=98}}</ref> * Peripheral venous thrombosis<ref name="NCBI"/> * Recurrent fever<ref name="NCBI"/> * Chills<ref name="NCBI"/> * Hemoptysis<ref name="NCBI"/> * [[Cough]]<ref name="NCBI"/> ==Diagnosis== {{Empty section|date=September 2017}} ==Management== {{Empty section|date=September 2017}}
