'''Refusal skills''' are a set of skills designed to help children avoid participating in high-risk behaviors.  Programs designed to discourage [[crime]], [[Recreational drug use|drug use]], [[violence]], and/or [[Human sexual activity|sexual activity]] frequently include refusal skills in their curricula to help students resist [[peer pressure]] while maintaining self-respect.  One such program is [[Drug Abuse Resistance Education]].  Programs may focus on: offering alternative activities, saying "no", being honest, and using humor.

