'''The Cabin Sydney''' is an outpatient [[addiction treatment]] clinic. The facility has been recognized as the first multinational addiction treatment provider in Australia. The Cabin Sydney is an affiliate of The Cabin Addiction Services Group. The Cabin Addiction Services Group also owns [[The Cabin Chiang Mai]] inpatient rehab. The Cabin Sydney opened in July 2015 and is located in Sydney, Australia.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/health/hidden-addiction-life-as-a-high-functioning-alcoholic/story-fneuzlbd-1227464631789 | title = Hidden addiction: Life as a high-functioning alcoholic | publisher = News.com.au | date = 1 July 2015 | accessdate = 28 September 2015 | author = Burke, Liz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-22/australians-addicted-to-ice-seeking-rehabilitation-in-thailand/6397992 | title = Ice addiction: Growing numbers of Australians travelling to Thai drug rehabilitation centres | publisher = Abc.net.au | date = 30 April 2015 | accessdate = 28 September 2015 | author = Jones, Ruby}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mmdnewswire.com/the-cabin-sydney-131286.html | title = The Cabin Sydney - the First Multinational Addiction Treatment Provider to Offer Services in Australia | publisher = Mmdnewswire.com | date = 1 July 2015 | accessdate = 28 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/northern-beaches/statistics-show-dramatic-spike-in-drug-offences-in-pittwater-over-two-year-period/story-fngr8hax-1227471280106 | title = Statistics show dramatic spike in drug offences in Pittwater over two year period | publisher = Dailytelegraph.com.au | date = 5 August 2015 | accessdate = 28 September 2015 | author = Marks, Alison}}</ref> In July 2016, The Cabin Sydney completed a study which found that 70% of [[crystal methamphetamine]] addicts required rehabilitation rather than jail.<ref>{{Cite news | work = Psychiatry Update | title = Ice addiction treatment 'hit and miss' | date = 11 July 2016 | author = Worsley Rachel}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | website = MedicalRepublic.com.au | title = Anti-ice campaign backfires | date = 13 July 2016 | author = Scully, Ruby Prosser | url = http://www.medicalrepublic.com.au/anti-ice-campaign-backfires/}}</ref> The Cabin Addiction Services Group also operates the Cabin Melbourne.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://radio.abc.net.au/programitem/pge6Qym8k6?play=true|title=Are Doctor-Shoppers Really at the Heart of Our Opioid Crisis? on Law Report|publisher=ABC|date=21 November 2018|access-date=20 February 2018}}</ref>
